</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged acts of intimidation and reprisals against a human rights defender for 
</p>
<p>cooperation with the United Nations Committee Against Torture (UNCAT). 
</p>
<p>According to the information received, in April 2014, Mr. Doros Polykarpou, 
</p>
<p>Executive Director of Action for Support, Equality and Antiracism (KISA), was 
</p>
<p>informed of an arrest warrant pending against him in relation to a parking fine. In 
</p>
<p>early May 2014, KISA had submitted an alternative report to UNCAT regarding 
</p>
<p>conditions in Mennogeia Detention Centre. On 26 May 2014, Mr. Polykarpou 
</p>
<p>received assurances that he could pay the fine by the end of May 2014. However, Mr. 
</p>
<p>Polykarpou was temporarily detained on 29 May 2014 while visiting the Mennogeia 
</p>
<p>Detention Centre. During his detention, he was handcuffed, denied access to drinking 
</p>
<p>water, and denied the right to contact his lawyer. He was released later that day. Mr. 
</p>
<p>Polykarpou was the subject of an earlier communication sent to Cyprus on 20 July 
</p>
<p>2011, see A/HRC/19/44, case no. CYP 1/2011. 
</p>
<p>05/08/2014 
