<p>According to the information received, on 26 January 2010, Mr. Sharif Mobley, a U.S. 
</p>
<p>citizen, was shot in his leg and seized by armed men in Sana&#8217;a. He was taken to the 
</p>
<p>Police Hospital in Sana&#8217;a where he was held incommunicado for 21 to 25 days and 
</p>
<p>interrogated by U.S. agents about his possible contact with a senior Al-Qaeda leader. 
</p>
<p>He was then held incommunicado in the Political Security prison and the Jumhori 
</p>
<p>Hospital for another three to four weeks. On 7 March 2010, Mr. Mobley allegedly 
</p>
<p>attempted to escape from the Jumhori hospital and killed a security guard in the 
</p>
<p>process. He was transferred to the Central Prison in Sana&#8217;a around September 2010 
</p>
<p>and has been charged with attempted murder. Mr. Mobley was last seen by his 
</p>
<p>lawyers at the Central Prison on 27 February 2014, after which his whereabouts have 
</p>
<p>become unknown.   
