<p>RUS 6/2014 
</p>
<p><b>Russian 
</b></p>
<p><b>Federation  
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Freedom of 
</b></p>
<p><b>expression;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Freedom of 
</b></p>
<p><b>peaceful assembly 
</b></p>
<p><b>and of association;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Human rights 
</b></p>
<p><b>defenders;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Allegations concerning an attack, smear campaign, stigmatization and acts of 
</p>
<p>intimidation against several human rights defenders working for organizations that 
</p>
<p>have their offices in the Human Rights House Voronezh (HRHV). According to the 
</p>
<p>information received, in late June 2014, signs bearing the names of organizations with 
</p>
<p>offices in HRHV were removed and vandalized. A banner was placed in Voronezh 
</p>
<p>with the phrase &#8220;The fifth column in Voronezh. These are traitors, scum and simply 
</p>
<p>freaks! Know their faces!&#8221; showing pictures of members of the HRHV, as well as 
</p>
<p>other human rights defenders of the city. Posters were also hung containing 
</p>
<p>information on the activities of members of the HRHV and LGBTI activists. On 1 
</p>
<p>July 2014, Mr. Andrey Yurov, honorary president of the International Youth Human 
</p>
<p>Rights Movement (IYHRM), which has its offices in the HRHV, was physically 
</p>
<p>assaulted by two masked men who threw an antiseptic liquid in his face, causing first 
</p>
<p>degree chemical burns. HRHV was the subject of two previous communications sent 
</p>
<p>on 21 January 2013, see A/HRC/23/51, case no. RUS 1/2013; and on 26 August 2013, 
</p>
<p>see A/HRC/25/74, case no. RUS 6/2013. 
