<p>BRA 6/2014 
</p>
<p><b>Brazil  
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Summary 
</b></p>
<p><b>executions;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Violence against 
</b></p>
<p><b>women;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Allegations of summary executions and acts of violence against women by Brazilian 
</p>
<p>security forces. According to the information received, since the beginning of 2014, 
</p>
<p>Brazilian security forces may have summarily executed more than 30 people in the 
</p>
<p>community of Acari (Rio de Janeiro) during military police operations. During these 
</p>
<p>operations, security forces reportedly destroyed people&#8217;s belongings, illegally entered 
</p>
<p>private houses, and threatened and beat women. Concerns are raised about the 
</p>
<p>indiscriminate use of firearms and the situation of women at risk during these 
</p>
<p>operations. Concern is also raised about the legal framework of police incursions in 
</p>
<p>private residences without legal warrants.  
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
