</b></p>
<p>Letter concerning the alleged arbitrary dismissal of the head of the World Intellectual 
</p>
<p>Property Organization (WIPO) staff association. According to the information 
</p>
<p>received, on 19 September 2014, Mr. Moncef Kateb, head of the staff association of 
</p>
<p>WIPO, was allegedly unfairly dismissed from his employment. It is reported that this 
</p>
<p>decision took place a few days before Mr. Kateb was expected to criticize some 
</p>
<p>management practices within the organization during WIPO&#8217;s annual governing body 
</p>
<p>meeting. Reportedly, the decision taken against Mr. Kateb is the latest in a series of 
</p>
<p>measures against him in recent years. 
