</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged killing of two members of the Ahmadiyya Muslim community in Pakistan. 
</p>
<p>According to the information received, on 22 September 2014, Mr. Mubashar Ahmad 
</p>
<p>Khosa Sahib, a 50-year-old Ahmadiyya Muslim from Satellite Town, Mirpur Khas, 
</p>
<p>was shot dead by two unknown motorcyclists. On 15 October 2014, Mr. Lateef Alam 
</p>
<p>Butt, a 62-year-old Ahmadiyya Muslim from Kamrah, District Attock, was shot dead 
</p>
<p>by unknown assailants when returning home from work. Mr. Alam Butt was a well-
</p>
<p>known Ahmadiyya Muslim and his house was a prayer centre for local members of 
</p>
<p>the Ahmadiyya Muslim community (Jamaat). The attack against Mr. Alam Butt took 
</p>
<p>place after Sipah-e-Sahaba, a banned extremist organization, announced plans to carry 
</p>
<p>out targeted killings of Ahmadiyya Muslims during a high-level internal meeting.  
