<p><b>Discrimination 
</b></p>
<p><b>against women ;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Letter concerning discriminatory provisions against women in nationality legislation. 
</p>
<p>According to the information received, current nationality law in Barbados 
</p>
<p>discriminates against women in that, although a child born in the country to either a 
</p>
<p>Barbadian father or mother acquires Barbadian nationality, only children born abroad 
</p>
<p>from Barbadian fathers, not mothers, can acquire Barbadian nationality. 
</p>
