<p>Alleged non-compliance with international human rights law and standards of 
</p>
<p>proposed amendments to the Rules of the House of Representatives of the United 
</p>
<p>States of America governing disclosure of funding received by non-governmental 
</p>
<p>organizations from foreign Governments. According to the information received, 
</p>
<p>during the 113th Congress, 2D session, a resolution was introduced to amend clause 
</p>
<p>(2)(g)(5) of rule XI of the Rules of the House of Representatives to require non-
</p>
<p>governmental organizations with witnesses appearing before committees of the House 
</p>
<p>to systemically disclose funding received from foreign Governments either during the 
</p>
<p>current fiscal year or two previous fiscal years.  
</p>
