<p>BRA 6/2013 
</p>
<p><b>Brazil  
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Business 
</b></p>
<p><b>enterprises;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Health;  Toxic 
</b></p>
<p><b>waste;  Water 
</b></p>
<p><b>and Sanitation;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged on-going contamination and poisoning in Piqui&#225; de Baixo, A&#231;ail&#226;ndia, 
</p>
<p>Maranh&#227;o State, Amazon Region, Brazil. According to information received, high levels 
</p>
<p>of pollutant emissions and contaminated water released by the iron and steel industry 
</p>
<p>operating in the vicinity of these communities have adversely affected their health and 
</p>
<p>livelihoods resulting in increased incidence of respiratory illnesses, eye and skin 
</p>
<p>maladies, and cancer. In particular, it is alleged that children died as a consequence of 
</p>
<p>the pollution through contact with incandescent slag, a toxic waste product of iron and 
</p>
<p>steel smelting. It is further reported that the affected communities lack access to health 
</p>
<p>services and recourse despite attempts at judicial resolutions.   
</p>
<p>05/11/2014 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
