</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged sentencing of a human rights defender as well as allegations of torture while in 
</p>
<p>detention. According to the information received, on 6 March 2014, a court reportedly 
</p>
<p>sentenced Mr. Tillaev to eight years and eight months of imprisonment on charges of 
</p>
<p>&#8220;trafficking in persons&#8221;. Mr. Tillaev was previously sentenced to administrative 
</p>
<p>detention on 20 September 2013 and released on 5 October 2013. While in detention, 
</p>
<p>Mr. Tillaev was reportedly tortured. On 2 January 2014, Mr. Tillaev was arrested on the 
</p>
<p>basis of an allegedly invalid arrest warrant. Grave concern is expressed at the severity of 
</p>
<p>this sentence, the reports of torture while in detention, and the alleged lack of due 
</p>
<p>process. Mr. Tillaev is a founding member of the Union of Independent Trade Unions, 
</p>
<p>which works in support of labour migrants.  
