</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Follow-up letter concerning alleged forced eviction of residents living in Jagatsinghpur 
</p>
<p>District, Odisha, India and surrounding areas. According to the information received, up 
</p>
<p>to 20, 000 people may be forced to leave their homes as a result of land being acquired 
</p>
<p>for the construction of an integrated steel plant and a captive port by Korean steel 
</p>
<p>corporation, Pohang Iron and Steel Corporation (POSCO). Reports suggest that the 
</p>
<p>construction of the steel plant will result in serious violations of the human rights of 
</p>
<p>affected people, including the right to an adequate standard of living, right to food, right 
</p>
<p>to adequate housing, right to water and sanitation, right to health, right to education, and 
</p>
<p>other related rights of people living in extreme poverty. Reports further indicate that the 
</p>
<p>rights of those opposing the project have been suppressed resulting in a series of human 
</p>
<p>rights abuses. 
</p>
<p>07/08/2014 
</p>
